2015-07~07
http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/security/612152/173-uighur-refugees-held-in-thailand-arrive-in-turkey

Bangkok Post
Suspected Uighurs from China's troubled far-western region of Xinjiang, rest inside a temporary shelter after they were detained at the immigration regional headquarters near the Thailand-Malaysia border in Hat Yai, Songkla province in March. Of the 220 held, 173 have been released and allowed to travel to Turkey. (Reuters photo)
Recep Akyol of the East Turkestan Migrants Association told The Associated Press the group, mostly women and children, arrived in Istanbul on June 30 and were being resettled in the central Turkish city of Kayseri, which boasts a strong Uighur community.

